The course gives an overview of client-centered marketing as a principle of managing business and cultural life. The means and methods for marketing plan for a cultrual event are examined.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of course is to give students basic knowledge in cultural marketing and drafting a marketing plan. During the course we advance students' competences in entrepreneurship, culture-related communication , creative thinking, skills of social media marketing, as well as expertise in planning and organising cultural events and projects.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Course graduates will be able to draw up marketing plans for cultural events including analyses of the situation and,
based on it, a plan of marketing measures as well as a media/communication plan.
After completing the course, a student:
has obtained entrepreneurial perspective;
is competent in culture-related communication;
has advanced one's creative thinking and skills of using social media;
is able to apply planning and organisational skills.
